   classification, (2) abstract and precise criteria for relevance
   classification in social media during disasters and emergencies, (3) the
   evaluation of a well-performing Random Forest algorithm for relevance
   classification incorporating metadata from social media into a batch
   learning approach (e.g., 91.28\%/89.19\% accuracy, 98.3\%/89.6\%
   precision and 80.4\%/87.5\% recall with a fast training time with
