   Traffic},
Booktitle = {DEBS'18: PROCEEDINGS OF THE 12TH ACM INTERNATIONAL CONFERENCE ON
   DISTRIBUTED AND EVENT-BASED SYSTEMS},
Year = {2018},
Pages = {198-201},
Abstract = {In this paper, we present our approach for solving the DEBS Grand
   Challenge 2018. The challenge asks to provide a prediction for (i) a
   destination and the (ii) arrival time of ships in a streaming-fashion
   using Geo-spatial data in the maritime context. Novel aspects of our
   approach include the use of ensemble learning based on Random Forest,
   Gradient Boosting Decision Trees (GBDT), XGBoost Trees and Extremely
   Randomized Trees (ERT) in order to provide a prediction for a
   destination while for the arrival time, we propose the use of
   Feed-forward Neural Networks. In our evaluation, we were able to achieve
   an accuracy of 97\% for the port destination classification problem and
   90\% (in minutes) for the ETA prediction.},
